WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.048 --> 00:00:07.757
[dramatic music playing]

2
00:00:07.758 --> 00:00:09.008
[Silvermane] <i>Gonna meet a new supplier</i>

3
00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:10.927
- at the docks tomorrow.
- It's not smart

4
00:00:10.928 --> 00:00:13.972
for you to go out in public
till we know who tried to take you out.

5
00:00:13.973 --> 00:00:15.223
You were saying Flint's your bodyguard.

6
00:00:15.224 --> 00:00:17.016
He protects me. and he's loyal.

7
00:00:17.017 --> 00:00:18.309
Are we gonna talk about the fact

8
00:00:18.310 --> 00:00:19.644
<i>that he turned into some kind
of sand monster?</i>

9
00:00:19.645 --> 00:00:22.897
[Cat] <i>Started about six months ago.
and it's been getting worse.</i>

10
00:00:22.898 --> 00:00:24.733
This little guy right over here: Addison.

11
00:00:24.734 --> 00:00:25.817
Can't say I've ever seen him.

12
00:00:25.818 --> 00:00:28.361
[Ben] <i>He's the guy that burned down
Silvermane's mansion.</i>

13
00:00:28.362 --> 00:00:30.739
[Robbie] <i>I am a reporter working a story
on James Addison's death.</i>

14
00:00:30.740 --> 00:00:33.116
- Jimmy's dead?
- He burned down the wrong house.

15
00:00:33.117 --> 00:00:35.076
I don't know who hired him.
His wife might.

16
00:00:35.077 --> 00:00:38.621
I got a hunch that you wouldn't want
the city's most ruthless gangster knowing

17
00:00:38.622 --> 00:00:41.666
that the money someone paid
your husband to kill him

18
00:00:41.667 --> 00:00:44.878
was being spent on lobster
and designer clothes.

19
00:00:44.879 --> 00:00:46.671
- Mister...?
- Carmedy.

20
00:00:46.672 --> 00:00:48.798
Okay. Carmedy.
my rate's ten dollars a day plus--

21
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:50.258
- But you'll get pictures.
- [Janet] Am I crazy

22
00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:53.052
- or is that the goddamn mayor of New York?
- [Robbie] <i>Cops had an ambush</i>

23
00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:54.846
<i>set up for Silvermane at the docks.</i>

24
00:00:54.847 --> 00:00:56.890
<i>Someone gave them a tip
about a booze exchange.</i>

25
00:00:56.891 --> 00:00:58.141
Cops were all set to catch the man himself

26
00:00:58.142 --> 00:01:00.685
<i>- in the act. but Silvermane never showed.</i>
- [yelling]

27
00:01:00.686 --> 00:01:03.230
What the hell did I just do?

28
00:01:05.983 --> 00:01:08.986
[desk scraping on floor]

29
00:01:12.031 --> 00:01:13.656
[Janet] So it's really settled?

30
00:01:13.657 --> 00:01:15.617
I'm not a fan of constant redecorating.

31
00:01:15.618 --> 00:01:16.826
I handled it.

32
00:01:16.827 --> 00:01:19.162
Silvermane won't be back around here.

33
00:01:19.163 --> 00:01:22.373
You know. this would go quicker
if either of you pitched in.

34
00:01:22.374 --> 00:01:23.458
- [grunts]
- [Robbie] Oh.

35
00:01:23.459 --> 00:01:25.502
- Oh. you needed help with that?
- [grunts]

36
00:01:25.503 --> 00:01:26.878
Seemed like a one-man job.

37
00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:28.421
Can't be that easy. can it?

38
00:01:28.422 --> 00:01:30.507
Not that I don't believe you. but--

39
00:01:30.508 --> 00:01:32.634
No. no. This was like that before.

40
00:01:32.635 --> 00:01:36.137
I am not talking about the desk
and you know it.

41
00:01:36.138 --> 00:01:38.598
[sighs] God.

42
00:01:38.599 --> 00:01:41.309
Imagine surviving a war
just to be killed at home.

43
00:01:41.310 --> 00:01:43.144
Addison didn't die a banker.

44
00:01:43.145 --> 00:01:44.813
I mean. the guy
torched things for a living.

45
00:01:44.814 --> 00:01:47.482
Besides. his wife knew
exactly what he was up to.

46
00:01:47.483 --> 00:01:51.194
She seemed to be doing just fine
living it up at the Geoffrey Hotel.

47
00:01:51.195 --> 00:01:52.904
Well. who wouldn't?

48
00:01:52.905 --> 00:01:54.698
[Robbie] Son of a bitch.

49
00:01:55.699 --> 00:01:57.492
I met this guy at the Hooverville.

50
00:01:57.493 --> 00:02:00.370
He's the one who pointed me
to Addison's widow.

51
00:02:00.371 --> 00:02:03.832
So he knows both Addison and Flint Marko.

52
00:02:03.833 --> 00:02:07.210
Two men with weird powers all of a sudden.
What are the chances?

53
00:02:07.211 --> 00:02:08.461
Exactly.

54
00:02:08.462 --> 00:02:09.963
I'm gonna go find this guy again.

55
00:02:09.964 --> 00:02:11.632
ask him some more questions.

56
00:02:13.092 --> 00:02:14.300
[door closes]

57
00:02:14.301 --> 00:02:16.553
What are you thinking about over there?

58
00:02:16.554 --> 00:02:20.348
I'm thinking I want you to check
if those three were ever POWs.

59
00:02:20.349 --> 00:02:22.100
Our units were segregated.

60
00:02:22.101 --> 00:02:26.020
So this guy couldn't have served directly
with Addison and Flint.

61
00:02:26.021 --> 00:02:27.439
So how come
they're all in the same picture?

62
00:02:29.817 --> 00:02:32.819
You know. sometimes I think
you forget I do this for a living.

63
00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:34.195
Mm. Can't imagine why.

64
00:02:34.196 --> 00:02:36.406
[knocking]

65
00:02:36.407 --> 00:02:38.409
- [tense music playing]
- [creaking]

66
00:02:39.785 --> 00:02:41.203
Ben Reilly?

67
00:02:45.416 --> 00:02:47.418
I come in peace.

68
00:02:48.878 --> 00:02:50.461
Finn Byrne.

69
00:02:50.462 --> 00:02:53.631
We haven't been formally introduced.
but...

70
00:02:53.632 --> 00:02:55.842
- we have someone in common.
- [Ben] In that case.

71
00:02:55.843 --> 00:02:57.927
uh. welcome?

72
00:02:57.928 --> 00:02:59.178
What happened to your muscle?

73
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.972
Couldn't find a woman to push around?

74
00:03:00.973 --> 00:03:03.684
I believe you owe the lady an apology.

75
00:03:08.939 --> 00:03:11.025
Come on. Reilly. I've got a job for you.

76
00:03:14.153 --> 00:03:16.155
[creaking]

77
00:03:20.409 --> 00:03:22.577
I'll take that apology now.

78
00:03:22.578 --> 00:03:24.288
[grunts]

79
00:03:25.998 --> 00:03:27.916
Why me?

80
00:03:27.917 --> 00:03:31.002
Why not. uh. Winston?

81
00:03:31.003 --> 00:03:32.629
Or one of your other guys?

82
00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:36.007
I have Winston looking into
where this Addison boy came from.

83
00:03:36.008 --> 00:03:37.634
Maybe there are others like him.

84
00:03:37.635 --> 00:03:40.136
After me little run-in
with your pal The Spider.

85
00:03:40.137 --> 00:03:43.556
I really see the value
of having friends with superpowers.

86
00:03:43.557 --> 00:03:44.767
Oh. yeah?

87
00:03:46.644 --> 00:03:48.478
[groans]

88
00:03:48.479 --> 00:03:52.482
All right. now. I need your help
with a rat problem.

89
00:03:52.483 --> 00:03:56.903
You see. somebody sent Addison
to burn down my house.

90
00:03:56.904 --> 00:04:01.616
And I'm assuming the same somebody tipped
off the cops about my booze shipment.

91
00:04:01.617 --> 00:04:02.700
Got any leads?

92
00:04:02.701 --> 00:04:05.162
You know. it's probably someone
on the inside.

93
00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:07.413
[sighs]

94
00:04:07.414 --> 00:04:09.415
I thought it might be a guy on my payroll.

95
00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:10.917
Flint Marko.

96
00:04:10.918 --> 00:04:13.878
He's been acting strange lately. too.

97
00:04:13.879 --> 00:04:16.381
But he didn't know
about the shipment. so...

98
00:04:16.382 --> 00:04:18.716
he's either in the clear

99
00:04:18.717 --> 00:04:20.970
or dead at the hands of the rat.

100
00:04:22.805 --> 00:04:25.723
I want you to find out who it is.

101
00:04:25.724 --> 00:04:28.142
Start with the police raid.

102
00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:30.353
Someone always gets paid.

103
00:04:30.354 --> 00:04:33.232
But the only thing
you can trust is human nature.

104
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:37.068
[groans] Jesus. [sniffs]

105
00:04:37.069 --> 00:04:39.112
Remember.

106
00:04:39.113 --> 00:04:40.739
people lie. Reilly.

107
00:04:42.241 --> 00:04:44.785
Only money tells the truth.

108
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:47.496
A retainer.

109
00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:51.083
There'll be a bonus if you finish the job.

110
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:56.421
- [door closes]
- So that's how you fixed it--

111
00:04:56.422 --> 00:04:57.630
we work for him now?

112
00:04:57.631 --> 00:04:59.757
Getting paid is better
than getting murdered.

113
00:04:59.758 --> 00:05:02.468
Hard to argue with that.

114
00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:04.679
"People lie. Only money tells the truth."

115
00:05:04.680 --> 00:05:05.763
The hell does that mean?

116
00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:08.057
Must be something
rich people say at cocktail parties.

117
00:05:08.058 --> 00:05:09.226
Not that I'll ever know.

118
00:05:10.227 --> 00:05:11.729
Wait a minute.

119
00:05:12.938 --> 00:05:14.355
What?

120
00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:16.066
You didn't know they made bills that big?

121
00:05:18.068 --> 00:05:19.610
I heard a rumor there's even 100.

122
00:05:19.611 --> 00:05:23.281
Crafty bastard marks all of his bills.

123
00:05:23.282 --> 00:05:25.575
Do we still have any of that money
from Cat Hardy?

124
00:05:25.576 --> 00:05:27.368
We ought to.

125
00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:30.329
Unless you've been sneaking off
to gamble it on horses.

126
00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:31.914
- Here.
- He's marking mine.

127
00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:33.542
He's probably marking hers.

128
00:05:35.878 --> 00:05:36.961
Anything?

129
00:05:36.962 --> 00:05:38.422
[Ben] Bingo.

130
00:05:43.385 --> 00:05:45.387
{\an8}[♪ Kirby sings "Saving Grace"]

131
00:05:52.728 --> 00:05:55.396
{\an8}<i>♪ The colors fading from the photograph ♪</i>

132
00:05:55.397 --> 00:05:57.148
<i>♪ I could tell the story ♪</i>

133
00:05:57.149 --> 00:05:59.817
<i>♪ but still you wouldn't know the half ♪</i>

134
00:05:59.818 --> 00:06:02.612
{\an8}<i>♪ This love was brought to life
from shards of glass ♪</i>

135
00:06:02.613 --> 00:06:04.697
{\an8}<i>♪ When you kiss me there's a shifting ♪</i>

136
00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:07.158
<i>♪ in the sepia tone ♪</i>

137
00:06:07.159 --> 00:06:10.369
{\an8}<i>♪ Can't escape the madness.
baby. magnetism ♪</i>

138
00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:13.706
{\an8}<i>♪ Run away but something
pulls me back into it ♪</i>

139
00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:16.834
{\an8}<i>♪ Lately I've been staring
at a broken mirror ♪</i>

140
00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:20.296
<i>♪ Needing someone to call my own ♪</i>

141
00:06:20.297 --> 00:06:23.508
<i>♪ Hey. lover ♪</i>

142
00:06:23.509 --> 00:06:26.385
{\an8}<i>♪ I need someone to save me now ♪</i>

143
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.638
{\an8}<i>♪ from all the pain ♪</i>

144
00:06:28.639 --> 00:06:31.099
{\an8}<i>♪ I suffer ♪</i>

145
00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:33.935
{\an8}<i>♪ and the heavy world
that weighs me down ♪</i>

146
00:06:33.936 --> 00:06:37.480
{\an8}<i>♪ 'Cause the world ain't sweet ♪</i>

147
00:06:37.481 --> 00:06:39.857
{\an8}<i>♪ It's bitter to taste ♪</i>

148
00:06:39.858 --> 00:06:41.234
{\an8}<i>♪ But you could be ♪</i>

149
00:06:41.235 --> 00:06:44.446
<i>♪ my saving grace ♪</i>

150
00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:52.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

151
00:07:05.801 --> 00:07:07.803
[song ends]

152
00:07:10.264 --> 00:07:13.933
- Newspapers! Come get your newspapers!
- [indistinct chatter]

153
00:07:13.934 --> 00:07:17.812
Seven police injured
in wild liquor raid on the docks.

154
00:07:17.813 --> 00:07:19.814
[continues indistinctly]

155
00:07:19.815 --> 00:07:21.357
Newspapers!

156
00:07:21.358 --> 00:07:24.110
- Come get your newspapers.
- [Ben muttering]

157
00:07:24.111 --> 00:07:25.403
That one. That one.

158
00:07:25.404 --> 00:07:27.947
[♪ Benny Goodman plays
"All the Cats Join In"]

159
00:07:27.948 --> 00:07:29.950
[clearing throat]

160
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:37.290
[coughing loudly]

161
00:07:37.291 --> 00:07:38.791
[groans]

162
00:07:38.792 --> 00:07:40.001
Are you hurt. sir?

163
00:07:40.002 --> 00:07:42.336
Years ago.
Caught a slug in the line of duty.

164
00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:45.214
and your good colleagues
at this very hospital saved my leg.

165
00:07:45.215 --> 00:07:47.592
God bless you all for the service
you provide this city.

166
00:07:47.593 --> 00:07:49.552
What's your name. sweetheart?

167
00:07:49.553 --> 00:07:52.513
Officer Batnick with
the Patrolman's Benevolent Association.

168
00:07:52.514 --> 00:07:54.432
Can I trouble you
for the room numbers of the boys

169
00:07:54.433 --> 00:07:56.100
that came in from last night's raid?

170
00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:57.226
Patrolman Jones

171
00:07:57.227 --> 00:07:58.728
- is right behind you. honey.
- Oh. thank you.

172
00:07:58.729 --> 00:08:00.731
♪ ♪

173
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:04.775
- [door closes]
- Patrolman Jones.

174
00:08:04.776 --> 00:08:07.236
Officer Batnick
with the Benevolent Association.

175
00:08:07.237 --> 00:08:09.405
Quite the scene
you walked into last night.

176
00:08:09.406 --> 00:08:10.781
Raiding the Silvermane shipment.

177
00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:11.991
You're a very brave man.

178
00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:13.117
Doesn't feel like it.

179
00:08:13.118 --> 00:08:15.119
Now. I'm here on behalf of the union

180
00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:17.455
to ensure
that our city's esteemed officers

181
00:08:17.456 --> 00:08:19.165
are properly compensated
for their injuries.

182
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:22.418
After all. a patrolman only goes
where he's told. right?

183
00:08:22.419 --> 00:08:24.754
Glad someone understands how it works.

184
00:08:24.755 --> 00:08:26.464
You got no choice in the matter.

185
00:08:26.465 --> 00:08:27.757
Been there. see?

186
00:08:27.758 --> 00:08:28.966
Orders are orders.

187
00:08:28.967 --> 00:08:30.551
See?

188
00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:32.804
So who told you where to go?

189
00:08:33.847 --> 00:08:35.223
Sergeant Miller.

190
00:08:35.224 --> 00:08:37.558
- [lighter flicks]
- You know.

191
00:08:37.559 --> 00:08:39.727
when things go wrong in the field.

192
00:08:39.728 --> 00:08:44.148
the higher-ups wind up carrying the can
for the injuries to their men.

193
00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:47.610
Friend to friend. you could be in
for a little trouble down the road.

194
00:08:47.611 --> 00:08:49.571
Especially with guys like Jones.

195
00:08:50.656 --> 00:08:51.739
Jones?

196
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:53.032
What the hell did Jones say?

197
00:08:53.033 --> 00:08:55.493
These raids.
they're meant to take weeks of prep.

198
00:08:55.494 --> 00:08:57.203
All we got was a measly couple hours.

199
00:08:57.204 --> 00:08:58.788
Pinning it on me is bullshit.

200
00:08:58.789 --> 00:09:01.332
If they want to blame anyone.
you should be talking to--

201
00:09:01.333 --> 00:09:02.500
Lieutenant Dunn.

202
00:09:02.501 --> 00:09:05.503
Let's just call it what it was.
a total shit show.

203
00:09:05.504 --> 00:09:09.090
Brave men sent to ambush
our city's toughest mobster

204
00:09:09.091 --> 00:09:12.176
with little time or information
now lay injured all over this hospital.

205
00:09:12.177 --> 00:09:13.427
Does that sound fair to them?

206
00:09:13.428 --> 00:09:15.429
I get orders like everybody else.

207
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:17.306
Think you can say no
to the chief of police?

208
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:18.391
Like to see you try.

209
00:09:18.392 --> 00:09:20.643
Do I need to remind you
that you're lying on your stomach

210
00:09:20.644 --> 00:09:22.979
with a bullet stuck in your ass?!

211
00:09:22.980 --> 00:09:25.773
When the chief tells you these orders
came straight from Mayor Morris.

212
00:09:25.774 --> 00:09:27.650
there are no questions left to ask.

213
00:09:27.651 --> 00:09:30.112
The mayor himself. huh?

214
00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:35.116
It's no good. It's broken.

215
00:09:35.117 --> 00:09:37.243
Two payphones down this morning.

216
00:09:37.244 --> 00:09:39.913
this one and the one across
from the delicatessen.

217
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:42.623
If it ain't one thing. it's another.

218
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:43.708
[chuckles] Yeah.

219
00:09:43.709 --> 00:09:45.835
I tell you. when Harriet told me
Gimbels was hiring.

220
00:09:45.836 --> 00:09:47.086
I raced down here.

221
00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:48.546
Didn't even stop to change my stockings.

222
00:09:48.547 --> 00:09:51.507
And then I got on the subway
and the guy goes. "Ten cents."

223
00:09:51.508 --> 00:09:52.591
- Get out of--
- [phone rings]

224
00:09:52.592 --> 00:09:54.302
[picks up phone]

225
00:09:54.303 --> 00:09:56.095
Hello? Okay.

226
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:58.180
756 West 57th.

227
00:09:58.181 --> 00:09:59.975
Got it. Thanks. Janet.

228
00:10:04.438 --> 00:10:05.439
I lied.

229
00:10:08.025 --> 00:10:10.027
[mysterious music playing]

230
00:10:11.278 --> 00:10:12.945
[Robbie] Scuse me. Scuse me. ma'am.

231
00:10:12.946 --> 00:10:14.947
- Ma'am. a moment of your time?
- [dog barking in distance]

232
00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:16.950
[indistinct chatter]

233
00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:26.667
Say. brother. you seen...

234
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:28.879
big Black motherfucker about this tall?

235
00:10:30.547 --> 00:10:32.089
[whistle blowing]

236
00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:33.382
On authority of Mayor Morris.

237
00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:35.176
this illegal camp's to be cleared!

238
00:10:35.177 --> 00:10:36.594
[indistinct shouting]

239
00:10:36.595 --> 00:10:37.887
Vacate immediately!

240
00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:40.015
- [shouting]
- Go!

241
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:45.186
[shouting]

242
00:10:45.187 --> 00:10:46.563
- Get over here!
- [grunting]

243
00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:50.149
[shouting]

244
00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.150
Get on the ground!

245
00:10:51.151 --> 00:10:52.819
[groaning]

246
00:10:53.612 --> 00:10:54.945
[woman screaming]

247
00:10:54.946 --> 00:10:56.197
Stop!

248
00:10:56.198 --> 00:10:58.116
Let go of me. Lonnie!

249
00:10:59.368 --> 00:11:01.410
Help me! Lonnie!

250
00:11:01.411 --> 00:11:02.995
Hey. Hey! Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey!

251
00:11:02.996 --> 00:11:04.622
Leave her be. now. Let her go.
We're all leaving.

252
00:11:04.623 --> 00:11:06.458
- [yells]
- [Lonnie groans]

253
00:11:07.542 --> 00:11:09.126
- [yells]
- [groans]

254
00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:11.671
[tense music playing]

255
00:11:14.049 --> 00:11:16.093
[shuddering]

256
00:11:18.220 --> 00:11:19.638
[grunts]

257
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:21.639
- [grunts]
- [groans]

258
00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:24.226
- [indistinct shouting]
- [man] He's a monster.

259
00:11:26.103 --> 00:11:27.144
Shit.

260
00:11:27.145 --> 00:11:29.313
I told you to get ou-- [grunting]

261
00:11:29.314 --> 00:11:30.565
What the hell?

262
00:11:31.566 --> 00:11:32.734
[grunts]

263
00:11:34.111 --> 00:11:35.987
[man] There's another one!

264
00:11:39.533 --> 00:11:41.075
- [grunts]
- I'm a reporter!

265
00:11:41.076 --> 00:11:42.576
- I'm with the <i>Bugle.</i>
- Who cares?

266
00:11:42.577 --> 00:11:43.536
- [whimpers]
- [grunts]

267
00:11:43.537 --> 00:11:44.579
- [yells]
- [grunts]

268
00:11:46.206 --> 00:11:48.124
- Take it easy now.
- Get him!

269
00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:50.544
- [grunting]
- [groaning]

270
00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:54.797
[grunting]

271
00:11:54.798 --> 00:11:55.756
[yells]

272
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:57.174
[grunts loudly]

273
00:11:57.175 --> 00:11:58.802
[grunting]

274
00:12:02.681 --> 00:12:05.224
[breathing heavily]

275
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:07.227
[horn honking in distance]

276
00:12:10.522 --> 00:12:11.856
- Hey.
- [snapping]

277
00:12:11.857 --> 00:12:14.692
I'm looking for a guy. Carmedy.

278
00:12:14.693 --> 00:12:15.776
You know him?

279
00:12:15.777 --> 00:12:17.361
Immense. Unctuous.

280
00:12:17.362 --> 00:12:19.113
More pinniped than human.

281
00:12:19.114 --> 00:12:21.240
Pinni-ped?

282
00:12:21.241 --> 00:12:23.200
He's so pinniped-like.
you wouldn't believe it.

283
00:12:23.201 --> 00:12:24.161
Mm.

284
00:12:26.621 --> 00:12:28.414
He's a big guy.

285
00:12:28.415 --> 00:12:29.874
Smells like sauerkraut.

286
00:12:29.875 --> 00:12:30.958
Well?

287
00:12:30.959 --> 00:12:33.002
You're talking about Hicks.

288
00:12:33.003 --> 00:12:34.753
Apartment four.

289
00:12:34.754 --> 00:12:36.006
[chuckling]

290
00:12:37.007 --> 00:12:38.967
Temperance begins with faith.

291
00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:41.760
[groans]

292
00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.221
[knocking]

293
00:12:45.474 --> 00:12:47.475
- [creaking]
- Oh. no.

294
00:12:47.476 --> 00:12:48.684
No. [grunts]

295
00:12:48.685 --> 00:12:51.061
No. Ow!

296
00:12:51.062 --> 00:12:52.396
Ow! [grunts]

297
00:12:52.397 --> 00:12:53.481
Ow!

298
00:12:53.482 --> 00:12:54.608
[grunts] Ow.

299
00:12:55.609 --> 00:12:56.692
[groans]

300
00:12:56.693 --> 00:12:58.360
Gosh. I hope your arm's okay.

301
00:12:58.361 --> 00:13:00.112
But closing a door on a guy--

302
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:01.697
is that how you treat a friend?

303
00:13:01.698 --> 00:13:03.699
That's not what we are.

304
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:05.075
And here I thought
we could braid each other's hair.

305
00:13:05.076 --> 00:13:07.036
Now. I've got a few questions.

306
00:13:07.037 --> 00:13:08.120
Be a good boy

307
00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:10.206
- and I'll pay you for your trouble.
- [sighs]

308
00:13:10.207 --> 00:13:12.041
- Well. go on then.
- Who hired you

309
00:13:12.042 --> 00:13:14.210
to get those photos
of the mayor and Cat Hardy?

310
00:13:14.211 --> 00:13:15.586
Nobody hired me.

311
00:13:15.587 --> 00:13:17.046
I'm a smut merchant.

312
00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:19.590
Mayor cheats on wife with lounge singer?

313
00:13:19.591 --> 00:13:20.883
During an election?

314
00:13:20.884 --> 00:13:23.219
Anybody would tell you that's a doozy.

315
00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:24.970
Would've gotten them myself. too. but...

316
00:13:24.971 --> 00:13:26.055
[knocking]

317
00:13:26.056 --> 00:13:28.224
How'd you know it was happening?

318
00:13:28.225 --> 00:13:31.352
I got a tip from Morris's office
that he scheduled a meeting with the girl.

319
00:13:31.353 --> 00:13:32.728
He called her?

320
00:13:32.729 --> 00:13:34.480
She called him.

321
00:13:34.481 --> 00:13:35.648
I'd meet with her. too. Wouldn't you?

322
00:13:35.649 --> 00:13:37.900
[muffled pulsing. warbling]

323
00:13:37.901 --> 00:13:39.361
[Carmedy speaks indistinctly]

324
00:13:40.445 --> 00:13:42.655
I thought it'd be a gold mine.

325
00:13:42.656 --> 00:13:44.323
Sell 'em to the papers. you know.

326
00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:45.950
or-or the mayor himself.

327
00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:47.868
Could get out of this shithole.

328
00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:49.162
Here we are.

329
00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:53.374
Is there a back way out of here?

330
00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:55.293
[tense music playing]

331
00:13:59.965 --> 00:14:01.674
[lock turns]

332
00:14:01.675 --> 00:14:03.425
[♪ Dinah Shore sings "Dearly Beloved"]

333
00:14:03.426 --> 00:14:04.552
Ever heard of a telephone?

334
00:14:04.553 --> 00:14:06.762
Trying to save a nickel.

335
00:14:06.763 --> 00:14:08.764
Handsome and thrifty.

336
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:10.432
Is he thirsty. too?

337
00:14:10.433 --> 00:14:12.644
I won't say no.

338
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:15.437
<i>♪ How clearly ♪</i>

339
00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.399
<i>♪ I see ♪</i>

340
00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:20.901
<i>♪ Somewhere in heaven ♪</i>

341
00:14:20.902 --> 00:14:22.027
[grunts]

342
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:25.282
<i>♪ you were fashioned for me ♪</i>

343
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:28.534
<i>♪ Angel eyes...</i>

344
00:14:28.535 --> 00:14:30.119
It's a bit much. isn't it?

345
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:31.829
Doesn't feel like you.

346
00:14:31.830 --> 00:14:34.039
I imagined something with a bit more...

347
00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:35.458
- edge.
- Ah.

348
00:14:36.459 --> 00:14:38.794
So we're imagining things now?

349
00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:40.797
Find me someone who wouldn't.

350
00:14:42.757 --> 00:14:43.882
[sighs]

351
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.676
So...

352
00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:47.595
have you found Flint?

353
00:14:47.596 --> 00:14:50.973
Working a few leads.
but nothing. uh. concrete.

354
00:14:50.974 --> 00:14:53.892
Could've said that
before I got you the drink.

355
00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:55.478
I can always find a reason to linger.

356
00:14:56.646 --> 00:14:58.689
Fact is. I had to take a pause on Flint.

357
00:14:58.690 --> 00:15:02.861
Silvermane turned up today
and hired me to find a rat in his crew.

358
00:15:06.865 --> 00:15:08.866
You didn't like hearing that.

359
00:15:08.867 --> 00:15:10.993
The part where you're not doing the job
I hired you for?

360
00:15:10.994 --> 00:15:13.454
Or the part where you're working
for Silvermane?

361
00:15:13.455 --> 00:15:15.040
I don't like either.

362
00:15:16.374 --> 00:15:19.543
You see. this place doesn't feel like me.

363
00:15:19.544 --> 00:15:21.128
Because it's not mine.

364
00:15:21.129 --> 00:15:23.797
There is nothing Silvermane didn't choose.

365
00:15:23.798 --> 00:15:26.091
And if he gave it to me.

366
00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:27.843
then he can take it all away.

367
00:15:27.844 --> 00:15:29.928
And then some.

368
00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:32.890
Any chance your boy Flint's
involved in betraying him

369
00:15:32.891 --> 00:15:34.224
and that's why he disappeared?

370
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:36.143
No. Flint is loyal to a fault.

371
00:15:36.144 --> 00:15:37.936
- What about the mayor?
- What about him?

372
00:15:37.937 --> 00:15:39.647
Booze is Silvermane's bread and butter.

373
00:15:39.648 --> 00:15:42.107
Mayor's calling for an end to prohibition.
bragging about the raid.

374
00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:45.028
Doesn't look good. you fraternizing
with the enemy the other night.

375
00:15:46.112 --> 00:15:47.155
I'm trying to help you.

376
00:15:48.239 --> 00:15:50.407
- Anything you want to tell me?
- Sure.

377
00:15:50.408 --> 00:15:52.409
I'm scared.

378
00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:53.952
You would be. too.

379
00:15:53.953 --> 00:15:55.454
Maybe you've forgotten.

380
00:15:55.455 --> 00:16:00.626
but Silvermane didn't get to where he is
by being calm and rational.

381
00:16:00.627 --> 00:16:03.838
He'll get rid of 50 if it means
he's sure he's got the one.

382
00:16:05.340 --> 00:16:08.051
It's too easy to get caught
in the crossfire when that happens.

383
00:16:09.094 --> 00:16:10.595
Try to remember that.

384
00:16:11.763 --> 00:16:13.223
If not for me...

385
00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:18.311
...then for you.

386
00:16:20.939 --> 00:16:22.856
[song ends]

387
00:16:22.857 --> 00:16:24.025
[exhales]

388
00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:30.448
[grunts]

389
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:34.327
[creaking]

390
00:16:48.591 --> 00:16:49.883
[mysterious music playing]

391
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:52.469
[Winston] Reilly. What are you doing here?

392
00:16:52.470 --> 00:16:53.804
Well. well. well.

393
00:16:53.805 --> 00:16:56.932
If it ain't Mr. Whiskers
searching for some cheese.

394
00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:59.309
And what the hell
is that supposed to mean?

395
00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.894
Your boss sent you out looking for supers.

396
00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:02.813
but here you are instead
covering your tracks.

397
00:17:02.814 --> 00:17:05.233
just like a rat. huh. Mr. Whiskers?

398
00:17:06.234 --> 00:17:08.485
You need to watch your mouth.

399
00:17:08.486 --> 00:17:10.112
- I have heard that. yes.
- I don't care

400
00:17:10.113 --> 00:17:12.114
if Silvermane hired you.

401
00:17:12.115 --> 00:17:13.574
I'm gonna find the rat.

402
00:17:13.575 --> 00:17:15.242
put him in the ground.

403
00:17:15.243 --> 00:17:18.620
Must sting.
not being trusted by the big boss anymore.

404
00:17:18.621 --> 00:17:21.039
He'll know he can trust me soon enough.

405
00:17:21.040 --> 00:17:23.542
Well. if you need a little help
from a professional in that effort.

406
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:25.335
I could speed things up a bit.

407
00:17:25.336 --> 00:17:27.379
Maybe even share what I find.

408
00:17:27.380 --> 00:17:29.382
Not for nothing. of course.

409
00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:33.511
There's nothing worse
than a man that's only loyal to money.

410
00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:40.809
You find anything.

411
00:17:40.810 --> 00:17:43.812
I don't care whose favorite
lounge singer they are.

412
00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:45.440
you come to me first.

413
00:17:49.861 --> 00:17:51.571
Come on. Gio.

414
00:17:56.993 --> 00:17:59.412
♪ ♪

415
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:04.666
[Robbie] <i>And nobody could stop him.</i>

416
00:18:04.667 --> 00:18:07.252
I mean. at one point.
he had half a dozen cops on him

417
00:18:07.253 --> 00:18:08.337
- whacking him with nightsticks...
- [door closes]

418
00:18:08.338 --> 00:18:09.922
...but he was indestructible.

419
00:18:09.923 --> 00:18:11.381
[Ben] Who?

420
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:12.800
The guy from the picture.

421
00:18:12.801 --> 00:18:16.804
His name is Lonnie Lincoln.
Turns out he's got powers. too.

422
00:18:16.805 --> 00:18:19.932
I mean. cops were attacking him. but he
was swatting 'em off like it was nothing.

423
00:18:19.933 --> 00:18:22.142
And Flint. My God. man.

424
00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:24.895
- His hands were like boulders.
- Wait. wait. Flint?

425
00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:26.688
You're saying Flint Marko was there?

426
00:18:26.689 --> 00:18:28.398
He sure was.

427
00:18:28.399 --> 00:18:29.858
Say. can I borrow your darkroom?

428
00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:32.110
I was the only reporter there.
and the story is mine.

429
00:18:32.111 --> 00:18:33.612
as long as nobody poaches it.

430
00:18:33.613 --> 00:18:35.697
This could be my ticket back to the <i>Bugle.</i>

431
00:18:35.698 --> 00:18:36.782
[Janet] Here's something

432
00:18:36.783 --> 00:18:38.867
for your story.
Ben's hunch was right.

433
00:18:38.868 --> 00:18:42.372
Marko. Addison. and your Lincoln fella
were all POWs together.

434
00:18:44.082 --> 00:18:45.624
That photo Ben found

435
00:18:45.625 --> 00:18:47.334
was from the day they were rescued.

436
00:18:47.335 --> 00:18:48.794
Darkroom. Photos.

437
00:18:48.795 --> 00:18:50.088
Right now.

438
00:18:51.548 --> 00:18:52.966
[door opens]

439
00:18:55.301 --> 00:18:57.344
[creaking]

440
00:18:57.345 --> 00:18:59.179
Hunch. huh?

441
00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:03.517
We both know three POWs
from the same camp with super abilities

442
00:19:03.518 --> 00:19:04.601
isn't a coincidence.

443
00:19:04.602 --> 00:19:05.686
So what aren't you telling me?

444
00:19:05.687 --> 00:19:07.479
I can't get into it right now.

445
00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:08.564
Seriously?

446
00:19:08.565 --> 00:19:11.024
Suddenly you're not the only guy
in New York with powers

447
00:19:11.025 --> 00:19:12.901
and you can't get into it right now?

448
00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.611
- I have to fix something.
- No. no.

449
00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:16.071
None of this cryptic shit.

450
00:19:16.072 --> 00:19:18.115
- What the hell is going on?
- Silvermane

451
00:19:18.116 --> 00:19:20.075
hired me to find the rat in his crew.

452
00:19:20.076 --> 00:19:21.743
and it's Cat Hardy.

453
00:19:21.744 --> 00:19:23.287
The singer?

454
00:19:23.288 --> 00:19:25.372
- How do you know?
- She's been meeting with the mayor.

455
00:19:25.373 --> 00:19:27.040
and then he called for the raid.

456
00:19:27.041 --> 00:19:29.084
She's close with Flint.
and he served with Addison.

457
00:19:29.085 --> 00:19:30.627
- You sure?
- She's the only one

458
00:19:30.628 --> 00:19:32.296
who connects all the pieces.

459
00:19:32.297 --> 00:19:33.672
Wow. that is bold.

460
00:19:33.673 --> 00:19:35.173
Winston's only a step away.

461
00:19:35.174 --> 00:19:38.427
and if he finds out she was behind it.

462
00:19:38.428 --> 00:19:40.137
he'll kill her.

463
00:19:40.138 --> 00:19:41.931
[dramatic music playing]

464
00:19:43.892 --> 00:19:47.519
I need Vera Addison's room number
at the Geoffrey.

465
00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:49.397
I have a plan.

466
00:19:50.899 --> 00:19:53.443
- [indistinct chatter]
- [newsie] Extra. extra! Read all about it!

467
00:19:55.695 --> 00:19:58.322
Mayor cracking down on Hooverville!

468
00:19:58.323 --> 00:20:01.366
[tense music playing]

469
00:20:01.367 --> 00:20:03.285
Peanuts! Hot roasted peanuts here!

470
00:20:03.286 --> 00:20:05.288
♪ ♪

471
00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.541
[cool music playing]

472
00:20:11.711 --> 00:20:14.338
- [indistinct chatter]
- [vendor] Here you go. sir.

473
00:20:14.339 --> 00:20:15.714
[newsie] Extra!

474
00:20:15.715 --> 00:20:17.382
Three for a nickel!

475
00:20:17.383 --> 00:20:19.385
♪ ♪

476
00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:30.772
[horn honks]

477
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:33.649
Extra!

478
00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:34.943
Read all about it.

479
00:20:35.944 --> 00:20:37.277
[vendor] Peanuts!

480
00:20:37.278 --> 00:20:39.029
Hot roasted peanuts here!

481
00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:40.530
[newsie] Murderers' Row ready for Boston!

482
00:20:40.531 --> 00:20:42.199
Read all about it!

483
00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.076
[tense music playing]

484
00:20:44.077 --> 00:20:46.120
Get your goddamn paws off me.

485
00:20:47.205 --> 00:20:49.499
Take it easy. pal.
I'm just trying to make a living.

486
00:20:51.376 --> 00:20:53.210
[newsie] Extra. extra!

487
00:20:53.211 --> 00:20:55.128
Read all about it!

488
00:20:55.129 --> 00:20:57.756
♪ ♪

489
00:20:57.757 --> 00:20:59.759
[cool music playing]

490
00:21:11.729 --> 00:21:14.982
I'd say "Don't be alarmed. Vera."
but you don't appear to be.

491
00:21:14.983 --> 00:21:16.775
What do you want?

492
00:21:16.776 --> 00:21:19.194
Questions about your husband's last job.

493
00:21:19.195 --> 00:21:21.363
Specifically who hired him.

494
00:21:21.364 --> 00:21:22.990
I'm not interested in talking.

495
00:21:22.991 --> 00:21:25.367
I wasn't with the last guy.
and I'm not now.

496
00:21:25.368 --> 00:21:27.662
Even if you're the one in danger?

497
00:21:28.830 --> 00:21:30.748
[whistling]

498
00:21:33.710 --> 00:21:35.585
Let me make this easier for you.

499
00:21:35.586 --> 00:21:37.921
What if I told you I knew

500
00:21:37.922 --> 00:21:39.549
that it was Cat Hardy?

501
00:21:40.842 --> 00:21:43.468
If I know. then the others
will find out soon enough.

502
00:21:43.469 --> 00:21:46.054
Best thing you can do
is leave town. and fast.

503
00:21:46.055 --> 00:21:49.391
Silvermane will kill you
to get that information.

504
00:21:49.392 --> 00:21:51.518
Or pay me.

505
00:21:51.519 --> 00:21:54.771
I'm not stupid. mister.
You're here for her. not me.

506
00:21:54.772 --> 00:21:57.566
And if you're protecting her.
I've got a proposition for you.

507
00:21:57.567 --> 00:22:00.110
- What's that?
- You pay me

508
00:22:00.111 --> 00:22:02.237
a thousand dollars. and I'm gone.

509
00:22:02.238 --> 00:22:04.072
A thousand?

510
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:05.949
I don't even know what that looks like.

511
00:22:05.950 --> 00:22:07.743
Mm.

512
00:22:07.744 --> 00:22:10.078
I bet Silvermane has that and then some.

513
00:22:10.079 --> 00:22:12.457
- I'll just tell him it's Cat myself.
- Slow down.

514
00:22:13.458 --> 00:22:15.751
I'll get you your money.

515
00:22:15.752 --> 00:22:18.755
You just stay out of trouble until then.

516
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:33.602
[door closes]

517
00:22:33.603 --> 00:22:35.688
What a dump.

518
00:22:38.107 --> 00:22:39.816
Get the man a drink.

519
00:22:39.817 --> 00:22:42.944
Educate yourself. Try the Green Spot.

520
00:22:42.945 --> 00:22:45.155
Ten-year-old Irish pot still whiskey.

521
00:22:45.156 --> 00:22:48.326
Not what you're used to.
but I'm sure you can live with it.

522
00:22:53.372 --> 00:22:55.500
[exhales] It'll do.

523
00:22:56.834 --> 00:22:58.877
You must think I'm out of touch.

524
00:22:58.878 --> 00:23:00.378
[Ben] Money. power?

525
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:05.175
Not a lot of it going around right now.
yet here you are in a castle tower.

526
00:23:05.176 --> 00:23:07.094
That's a testament to what you've built.

527
00:23:07.095 --> 00:23:11.516
It must be nice.
not having to look over your shoulder.

528
00:23:12.975 --> 00:23:17.437
So unconcerned with your possessions
'cause you have so little.

529
00:23:17.438 --> 00:23:21.234
You'd be surprised at how much people
will fight for what little they have.

530
00:23:23.444 --> 00:23:25.529
Do you know what entropy is. Reilly?

531
00:23:25.530 --> 00:23:28.365
The universe trends to disorder.

532
00:23:28.366 --> 00:23:29.867
Can't help itself.

533
00:23:30.910 --> 00:23:33.954
All you can do is fight
to keep the chaos from your door.

534
00:23:33.955 --> 00:23:35.789
[dark music playing]

535
00:23:35.790 --> 00:23:38.542
But like I said. you're lucky.

536
00:23:38.543 --> 00:23:41.419
You don't have anything
anyone wants to take. [laughs softly]

537
00:23:41.420 --> 00:23:43.631
Maybe not.

538
00:23:45.299 --> 00:23:48.553
But here's some friendly advice
all the same.

539
00:23:49.554 --> 00:23:51.847
Whoever the rat turns out to be.

540
00:23:51.848 --> 00:23:56.017
you can't be emotional about it.
even if it breaks your heart.

541
00:23:56.018 --> 00:23:59.437
And if someone should come to you
saying they have all the answers.

542
00:23:59.438 --> 00:24:01.065
know that they're lying.

543
00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:05.777
You know who it is. don't you?

544
00:24:05.778 --> 00:24:08.281
Doesn't matter what I know
until I can prove it.

545
00:24:10.283 --> 00:24:13.786
Well. the quicker you prove it.
the quicker they die.

546
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:16.788
So. what are you waiting for?

547
00:24:16.789 --> 00:24:18.331
Thanks for the drink.

548
00:24:18.332 --> 00:24:21.376
It was just what I needed.

549
00:24:21.377 --> 00:24:22.628
[web squishes]

550
00:24:26.924 --> 00:24:28.175
[Robbie] This is an exclusive. Walters.

551
00:24:28.176 --> 00:24:30.343
The <i>Bugle</i> will be
the only ones to have it.

552
00:24:30.344 --> 00:24:33.513
No one else was there.
I am the only one with these.

553
00:24:33.514 --> 00:24:34.891
Mm-hmm.

554
00:24:40.646 --> 00:24:42.480
- [door closes]
- How you been? You look good.

555
00:24:42.481 --> 00:24:44.232
Well. you know. I'm getting by.

556
00:24:44.233 --> 00:24:45.984
- Say. listen. I was hoping--
- Oh. you still got the eye.

557
00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:47.235
I'll give you that.

558
00:24:47.236 --> 00:24:50.155
Well. I'm the same guy I always been.

559
00:24:50.156 --> 00:24:52.240
- Tell me the story.
- So.

560
00:24:52.241 --> 00:24:53.950
the cops came in frothing at the mouth.

561
00:24:53.951 --> 00:24:55.702
Now. uh. Lincoln.

562
00:24:55.703 --> 00:24:57.412
uh. he was just trying
to help his neighbor.

563
00:24:57.413 --> 00:24:59.289
He and Marko. they're both veterans.

564
00:24:59.290 --> 00:25:04.545
But now they're living in a Hooverville
with these mysterious powers.

565
00:25:07.506 --> 00:25:09.633
Superpowers. Ah.

566
00:25:09.634 --> 00:25:11.009
Just like The Spider.

567
00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:12.469
Before the asshole
decided to take a powder.

568
00:25:12.470 --> 00:25:14.971
Someone should've told him
a depression was coming. [laughs]

569
00:25:14.972 --> 00:25:18.350
- [laughs]
- Now you are bringing me two of them?

570
00:25:18.351 --> 00:25:19.893
The public can't get enough of this stuff.

571
00:25:19.894 --> 00:25:21.853
The papers will sell like crazy.

572
00:25:21.854 --> 00:25:23.772
Write it up.

573
00:25:23.773 --> 00:25:25.523
I want to go with this
in the next edition.

574
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:28.068
Say. am I getting my old desk back
to write it at?

575
00:25:28.069 --> 00:25:30.779
Well. let's not run
before we can walk. huh?

576
00:25:30.780 --> 00:25:34.824
Um. for now. it'll be off the books.
you know. on the QT.

577
00:25:34.825 --> 00:25:36.993
But you keep bringing me more like this.

578
00:25:36.994 --> 00:25:40.580
and then we can talk about
bringing you back full-time.

579
00:25:40.581 --> 00:25:43.000
Like those old Spider days. [chuckles]

580
00:25:47.255 --> 00:25:49.799
- Good to see you again. Walters.
- [laughs]

581
00:25:51.300 --> 00:25:53.343
- Open or closed?
- Uh. closed.

582
00:25:53.344 --> 00:25:54.470
Okay.

583
00:25:57.139 --> 00:26:00.225
[Ben] So. I want you to be me. You know.
like one of those guys in the movies.

584
00:26:00.226 --> 00:26:02.519
You know. Bogie. Cagney. uh. Eddie G.

585
00:26:02.520 --> 00:26:04.980
You know. you c-can wear the hat.
you can smoke a cigarette.

586
00:26:04.981 --> 00:26:06.189
Y-You're cool.

587
00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:08.483
I want you to be cool. Hey!

588
00:26:08.484 --> 00:26:10.902
Focus. And quit casing my place.

589
00:26:10.903 --> 00:26:12.404
I ain't doing nothing.

590
00:26:12.405 --> 00:26:14.239
I need to rely on you. Frankie.

591
00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:15.740
Can I rely on you?

592
00:26:15.741 --> 00:26:17.243
I'm your man.

593
00:26:24.041 --> 00:26:25.459
[suspenseful music playing]

594
00:26:51.235 --> 00:26:53.029
[snoring]

595
00:27:09.754 --> 00:27:11.964
- [creaking]
- [suspenseful music playing]

596
00:27:23.309 --> 00:27:25.018
[mobster] Anything?

597
00:27:25.019 --> 00:27:27.021
He's been up there all night.

598
00:27:28.856 --> 00:27:30.858
[quirky music playing]

599
00:27:38.908 --> 00:27:41.659
[radio host] <i>Calling all
junior detectives.</i>

600
00:27:41.660 --> 00:27:44.079
<i>Calling all junior detectives.</i>

601
00:27:44.080 --> 00:27:47.541
<i>Tonight's</i> Mystery Hour <i>is about to begin.</i>

602
00:27:48.542 --> 00:27:50.544
[snoring]

603
00:28:14.610 --> 00:28:16.487
[muffled pulsing. warbling]

604
00:28:21.575 --> 00:28:22.910
[amplified clicking]

605
00:28:38.008 --> 00:28:40.010
[Silvermane snorts]

606
00:28:42.430 --> 00:28:44.432
[atmospheric music playing]

607
00:29:08.706 --> 00:29:11.000
♪ ♪

608
00:29:17.298 --> 00:29:18.299
[wind gusts]

609
00:29:21.093 --> 00:29:22.803
Boys!

610
00:29:24.555 --> 00:29:25.973
Hey. boss?

611
00:29:29.435 --> 00:29:32.645
- Well?
- Balcony door was open.

612
00:29:32.646 --> 00:29:34.230
No one's here.

613
00:29:34.231 --> 00:29:36.441
Think it was the wind.

614
00:29:36.442 --> 00:29:38.194
All right. well. check it again.

615
00:29:39.195 --> 00:29:41.197
[tense music playing]

616
00:29:52.541 --> 00:29:54.168
All clear. boss.

617
00:30:16.190 --> 00:30:18.192
[indistinct chatter]

618
00:30:30.829 --> 00:30:32.831
[footsteps approaching]

619
00:30:44.760 --> 00:30:46.010
[laughs softly]

620
00:30:46.011 --> 00:30:47.846
I taught you well.

621
00:30:53.811 --> 00:30:55.895
I should shoot you for running away.

622
00:30:55.896 --> 00:30:58.065
Well. how about kissing me
for coming back?

623
00:31:00.609 --> 00:31:02.611
[dramatic music playing]

624
00:31:11.704 --> 00:31:14.747
I've been so scared. Flint.

625
00:31:14.748 --> 00:31:17.750
I didn't know where you were.
what was happening to you.

626
00:31:17.751 --> 00:31:19.544
It's all right.

627
00:31:19.545 --> 00:31:21.672
I never should have run. but I'm back now.

628
00:31:22.673 --> 00:31:24.841
Something has happened.

629
00:31:24.842 --> 00:31:26.676
With Silvermane.

630
00:31:26.677 --> 00:31:28.261
I'll talk to him.

631
00:31:28.262 --> 00:31:29.762
Whatever it is. it can be fixed.

632
00:31:29.763 --> 00:31:31.347
No. No. I don't want to fix it.

633
00:31:31.348 --> 00:31:33.182
And I don't care about Silvermane.

634
00:31:33.183 --> 00:31:34.684
- What?
- I don't care about what he wants.

635
00:31:34.685 --> 00:31:36.603
I don't care about
what you think you owe him.

636
00:31:36.604 --> 00:31:39.023
I just want us to be together.

637
00:31:40.107 --> 00:31:41.858
If you love me...

638
00:31:41.859 --> 00:31:45.528
- Don't start with that--
- If you really love me.

639
00:31:45.529 --> 00:31:49.617
you won't ask any questions.
you'll just leave with me right now.

640
00:31:54.371 --> 00:31:55.997
Done.

641
00:31:55.998 --> 00:31:57.665
Really?

642
00:31:57.666 --> 00:31:59.167
Yeah.

643
00:31:59.168 --> 00:32:00.377
Pack a bag.

644
00:32:05.007 --> 00:32:06.592
[ominous music playing]

645
00:32:17.603 --> 00:32:19.021
- [Flint grunts]
- Are you okay?

646
00:32:20.522 --> 00:32:21.773
- No...
- What's the matter?

647
00:32:21.774 --> 00:32:23.608
Why did you turn away from me?

648
00:32:23.609 --> 00:32:25.069
Nothing. It's nothing.

649
00:32:28.030 --> 00:32:29.864
No! No. no. no. Stop. Flint.

650
00:32:29.865 --> 00:32:32.367
- No. Flint! Stop. please! Please.
- I can't!

651
00:32:32.368 --> 00:32:33.576
I can't!

652
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:34.911
[tense music playing]

653
00:32:34.912 --> 00:32:36.664
There's no turning it off.

654
00:32:37.706 --> 00:32:39.290
There's no fixing me.

655
00:32:39.291 --> 00:32:41.668
- There has to be a way.
- [groans]

656
00:32:41.669 --> 00:32:43.086
We'll find a way.

657
00:32:43.087 --> 00:32:45.089
[panting]

658
00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:50.344
It's a fantasy.

659
00:32:52.346 --> 00:32:55.140
Kidding myself I could have this life.

660
00:32:56.141 --> 00:32:57.976
I could have you.

661
00:33:05.984 --> 00:33:07.361
- [crying]
- [door opens]

662
00:33:16.078 --> 00:33:17.662
You see this?

663
00:33:17.663 --> 00:33:19.914
They smashed up the cops.

664
00:33:19.915 --> 00:33:21.874
I'd have paid to see that.

665
00:33:21.875 --> 00:33:23.251
Reilly?

666
00:33:23.252 --> 00:33:24.878
He didn't leave all night.

667
00:33:27.631 --> 00:33:29.382
[Ben] That's right.

668
00:33:29.383 --> 00:33:31.677
Keep following me.

669
00:33:34.680 --> 00:33:36.806
I need you at The Alcove today.

670
00:33:36.807 --> 00:33:39.517
I want you to keep an eye
on Cat Hardy for me.

671
00:33:39.518 --> 00:33:42.645
And. uh. as promised.

672
00:33:42.646 --> 00:33:44.188
Look at me.

673
00:33:44.189 --> 00:33:46.524
- an honest working man.
- That's right.

674
00:33:46.525 --> 00:33:48.526
Now. if Ms. Hardy goes anywhere.

675
00:33:48.527 --> 00:33:49.944
I want to know about it.

676
00:33:49.945 --> 00:33:51.655
You got it. boss.

677
00:33:52.656 --> 00:33:55.283
That's right. folks.
Monsters in the streets.

678
00:33:55.284 --> 00:33:57.076
Get your copy while they last.

679
00:33:57.077 --> 00:34:00.372
Monsters on the loose.

680
00:34:01.373 --> 00:34:02.790
[Robbie] That...

681
00:34:02.791 --> 00:34:04.334
is not what I wrote.

682
00:34:05.335 --> 00:34:06.420
[mutters softly]

683
00:34:07.421 --> 00:34:10.798
"A routine sweep of a city Hooverville
revealed two violent monsters

684
00:34:10.799 --> 00:34:12.467
looking to harm all they came across..."

685
00:34:12.468 --> 00:34:14.469
I never called them monsters.

686
00:34:14.470 --> 00:34:16.763
"Only with the help
of our heroic police force

687
00:34:16.764 --> 00:34:19.056
did the residents escape
with their lives..."

688
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:21.809
See. that. that is not what happened.

689
00:34:21.810 --> 00:34:24.605
He took my name
and put it on a bunch of lies.

690
00:34:25.606 --> 00:34:27.607
The pictures are great.

691
00:34:27.608 --> 00:34:29.358
What?

692
00:34:29.359 --> 00:34:31.736
[quirky music playing]

693
00:34:31.737 --> 00:34:33.446
[Ben] One hundred. two hundred.

694
00:34:33.447 --> 00:34:34.530
three hundred.

695
00:34:34.531 --> 00:34:36.032
four hundred. five hundred.

696
00:34:36.033 --> 00:34:37.742
six hundred. seven hundred. eight hundred.

697
00:34:37.743 --> 00:34:40.078
nine hundred. a thousand.

698
00:34:42.748 --> 00:34:44.040
A deal's a deal.

699
00:34:44.041 --> 00:34:46.418
You know what to do.

700
00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:54.675
Oh. look at that. shiny apples. Here.

701
00:34:54.676 --> 00:34:56.761
- Here you go. All right.
- [vendor] Oh. <i>Grazie.</i>

702
00:34:56.762 --> 00:34:58.764
[tense music playing]

703
00:35:00.891 --> 00:35:02.725
Hey. buddy. that was my foot.

704
00:35:02.726 --> 00:35:03.894
<i>Mi scusi.</i>

705
00:35:17.825 --> 00:35:20.159
- [Cat over phone] <i>Hello?</i>
- It's Ben. I need to see you.

706
00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:21.577
Why?

707
00:35:21.578 --> 00:35:23.789
<i>I'll explain when I get there.
Just stay put.</i>

708
00:35:28.669 --> 00:35:30.294
Someone wants to talk to you.

709
00:35:30.295 --> 00:35:31.880
Well. I'm busy. They can wait.

710
00:35:32.965 --> 00:35:35.258
Unhand my shoulder or lose your nose.

711
00:35:35.259 --> 00:35:36.717
It's the mayor.

712
00:35:36.718 --> 00:35:38.720
♪ ♪

713
00:35:40.222 --> 00:35:41.848
I want a line to The Spider.

714
00:35:41.849 --> 00:35:44.016
The guy from five years ago?

715
00:35:44.017 --> 00:35:45.977
I thought he was dead.

716
00:35:45.978 --> 00:35:48.145
I happen to know he's alive and well.

717
00:35:48.146 --> 00:35:50.106
Well. then. you know more than I do.

718
00:35:50.107 --> 00:35:51.983
Look. don't play dumb with me. pal.

719
00:35:51.984 --> 00:35:54.277
Back in the day.
you were always in the right place

720
00:35:54.278 --> 00:35:56.237
to snap a picture of The Spider.

721
00:35:56.238 --> 00:35:59.407
Whatever your deal is with him.
that's your business.

722
00:35:59.408 --> 00:36:02.159
You just tell your buddy
that I need to talk to him.

723
00:36:02.160 --> 00:36:04.161
Crime is out of control.

724
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:06.831
People are scared.
and t-the city needs order.

725
00:36:06.832 --> 00:36:09.625
That why you're picking
a fight with Silvermane?

726
00:36:09.626 --> 00:36:12.253
Didn't he bankroll your first campaign?

727
00:36:12.254 --> 00:36:17.091
Silvermane is a ruthless criminal
who has squeezed this city long enough.

728
00:36:17.092 --> 00:36:20.011
Just get me in touch with The Spider.

729
00:36:20.012 --> 00:36:22.138
Make yourself a new friend.

730
00:36:22.139 --> 00:36:24.599
I can't wait.

731
00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:26.726
I believe in you. Ben Reilly.

732
00:36:26.727 --> 00:36:29.478
[Ben] Oh. my gosh. thank you so much.

733
00:36:29.479 --> 00:36:31.188
Where the hell you been?

734
00:36:31.189 --> 00:36:33.608
She took a cab to Penn Station
ten minutes ago.

735
00:36:33.609 --> 00:36:34.776
[exciting music playing]

736
00:36:37.237 --> 00:36:38.446
- [gasps]
- Just shush.

737
00:36:38.447 --> 00:36:40.073
Get out or you're coming with me.

738
00:36:44.536 --> 00:36:46.371
Penn Station on the double.

739
00:36:48.624 --> 00:36:50.459
♪ ♪

740
00:37:01.053 --> 00:37:02.387
Cat.

741
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:04.847
Why are you here?

742
00:37:04.848 --> 00:37:07.642
You really aren't a very good detective.
are you?

743
00:37:07.643 --> 00:37:09.852
You don't strike me
as the kind of woman who runs.

744
00:37:09.853 --> 00:37:11.812
Maybe I lost my last reason
to stick around.

745
00:37:11.813 --> 00:37:14.273
What do you say we cut the fancy talk?

746
00:37:14.274 --> 00:37:17.193
You found Addison through Flint
and paid him to bomb Silvermane's mansion.

747
00:37:17.194 --> 00:37:19.528
You tipped off Morris
about the booze shipment.

748
00:37:19.529 --> 00:37:23.366
You're Silvermane's rat.
The only thing I don't know is why.

749
00:37:23.367 --> 00:37:25.284
You know. you boys are all the same.

750
00:37:25.285 --> 00:37:29.080
You come up with your own little stories
and you make everyone else fit them.

751
00:37:29.081 --> 00:37:32.083
Silvermane treats me like a damn doll.
Flint thinks I'm afraid of him

752
00:37:32.084 --> 00:37:33.918
and you think I'm a killer.

753
00:37:33.919 --> 00:37:37.755
I am done with people telling me
who I am and what I get to do.

754
00:37:37.756 --> 00:37:39.924
- You ask me why I'm leaving?
- [Winston] Hey. Reilly.

755
00:37:39.925 --> 00:37:41.927
[suspenseful music playing]

756
00:37:43.345 --> 00:37:45.596
There you are.

757
00:37:45.597 --> 00:37:48.141
And look. a bonus.

758
00:37:49.184 --> 00:37:52.645
I guess I am the luckiest guy in New York.

759
00:37:52.646 --> 00:37:53.896
[sighs] Man.

760
00:37:53.897 --> 00:37:56.274
I should've known you were in it together.

761
00:37:57.275 --> 00:37:59.152
Now the boss can take care of both of you.

762
00:38:04.157 --> 00:38:05.742
Move.

763
00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:14.334
[train rattling on tracks]

764
00:38:30.559 --> 00:38:32.393
♪ ♪

765
00:38:32.394 --> 00:38:35.479
You know. dick. I got to give you credit.

766
00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:37.606
You came close.

767
00:38:37.607 --> 00:38:41.318
Too bad you couldn't get
the Addison widow out of town.

768
00:38:41.319 --> 00:38:44.155
I only had to slap her around
a little bit to get the truth.

769
00:38:44.156 --> 00:38:45.782
What a guy.

770
00:38:47.492 --> 00:38:50.912
Yeah. well. a prick to the end. huh?

771
00:38:52.205 --> 00:38:54.458
Might be the only thing I like about you.

772
00:39:00.047 --> 00:39:01.673
[engine turns off]

773
00:39:10.557 --> 00:39:12.559
♪ ♪

774
00:39:21.777 --> 00:39:25.362
[Winston] I caught them both
trying to skip town. boss.

775
00:39:25.363 --> 00:39:27.031
It looks like Reilly was in on it.

776
00:39:27.032 --> 00:39:28.867
The guy with all the answers.

777
00:39:33.080 --> 00:39:34.288
[gasps]

778
00:39:34.289 --> 00:39:37.334
You didn't think
you'd be seeing her again. did you?

779
00:39:38.335 --> 00:39:40.377
This is Addison's widow.

780
00:39:40.378 --> 00:39:43.255
She's also the only person who knows
who hired her dearly deceased husband.

781
00:39:43.256 --> 00:39:46.301
She didn't want to talk. but. uh...

782
00:39:48.512 --> 00:39:50.262
...she came around.

783
00:39:50.263 --> 00:39:51.723
Right? [chuckles]

784
00:39:53.433 --> 00:39:56.144
Hurry up. unless you want
to join your husband.

785
00:39:57.187 --> 00:39:58.688
- This is a--
- Quiet.

786
00:40:01.149 --> 00:40:03.859
Let's hear what the widow has to say.

787
00:40:03.860 --> 00:40:06.153
He told me it was Cat Hardy.

788
00:40:06.154 --> 00:40:08.990
That she paid him a thousand dollars
to burn down your mansion.

789
00:40:10.826 --> 00:40:12.368
[Winston] What'd I tell you. huh?

790
00:40:12.369 --> 00:40:15.372
You can dress up a stray dog
however you like. it'll still bite you.

791
00:40:16.414 --> 00:40:17.791
So you've said.

792
00:40:19.876 --> 00:40:21.253
It's not true.

793
00:40:22.254 --> 00:40:23.504
- It's not me.
- [Winston chuckles]

794
00:40:23.505 --> 00:40:25.674
Lying to the end. huh?

795
00:40:26.675 --> 00:40:29.552
I always knew
it was just a matter of time with you.

796
00:40:29.553 --> 00:40:32.138
It's a good story. I'll give you that.

797
00:40:32.139 --> 00:40:33.639
You got proof?

798
00:40:33.640 --> 00:40:36.142
Yeah. Show them.

799
00:40:36.143 --> 00:40:37.769
Come on.

800
00:40:42.899 --> 00:40:45.985
She couldn't quite manage to blow it all.

801
00:40:45.986 --> 00:40:47.695
Too bad. huh?

802
00:40:47.696 --> 00:40:49.364
[laughs]

803
00:40:57.789 --> 00:40:59.124
[laughs]

804
00:41:01.793 --> 00:41:03.461
[stifled laugh]

805
00:41:05.046 --> 00:41:07.423
Where does your money come from. Winston?

806
00:41:07.424 --> 00:41:09.550
[suspenseful music playing]

807
00:41:09.551 --> 00:41:11.385
From you.

808
00:41:11.386 --> 00:41:13.471
That's right. From me.

809
00:41:14.472 --> 00:41:17.058
And did you know that I mark all my bills?

810
00:41:20.604 --> 00:41:23.857
A different spot for every schmuck
on my payroll.

811
00:41:25.692 --> 00:41:27.611
Guess where I mark yours.

812
00:41:29.613 --> 00:41:31.864
What?

813
00:41:31.865 --> 00:41:33.408
That's not possible.

814
00:41:37.746 --> 00:41:40.790
<i>There's nothing worse than a man
who's only loyal to money.</i>

815
00:41:41.833 --> 00:41:43.584
You son of a bitch.

816
00:41:43.585 --> 00:41:45.461
[Vera] <i>I bet Silvermane has that
and then some.</i>

817
00:41:45.462 --> 00:41:47.297
<i>Maybe I'll go talk to him.</i>

818
00:41:48.340 --> 00:41:52.259
[Ben] <i>Crafty bastard
marks all of his bills.</i>

819
00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:53.595
You set me up?

820
00:41:54.596 --> 00:41:55.931
[Silvermane] <i>People lie. Reilly.</i>

821
00:41:56.932 --> 00:41:58.934
Only money tells the truth.

822
00:42:01.019 --> 00:42:03.979
It was him. He threatened
to kill me if I said otherwise.

823
00:42:03.980 --> 00:42:06.398
You lying bitch. I'll rip your goddamn--

824
00:42:06.399 --> 00:42:07.943
- [gunshot]
- [gasps]

825
00:42:15.033 --> 00:42:16.242
[clears throat]

826
00:42:16.243 --> 00:42:17.994
[gun cocks]

827
00:42:21.623 --> 00:42:24.209
You good with a shovel. Reilly?

828
00:42:25.669 --> 00:42:27.378
Why?

829
00:42:27.379 --> 00:42:30.048
We'll be needing another grave.

830
00:42:32.801 --> 00:42:34.803
[atmospheric music playing]

831
00:43:02.831 --> 00:43:04.833
♪ ♪

832
00:43:32.861 --> 00:43:34.863
♪ ♪

833
00:44:02.891 --> 00:44:04.893
♪ ♪

834
00:44:32.921 --> 00:44:34.923
♪ ♪

834
00:44:35.305 --> 00:45:35.646
Do you want subtitles for any video?
